OREON Conveyor Maintenance Manual

Scope: belt conveyors, drive pulleys, idlers, take-up systems, reducers, and drive motors.

Normal operation requires centered belt tracking, steady motor current, clean idlers, correct belt
tension, guarded nip points, and no belt edge fraying.

Misalignment indicators include belt mistracking, edge damage, high vibration at pulley bearings,
uneven idler wear, belt slip, and rising drive current. Corrective actions: isolate conveyor, inspect
pulley lagging, align idlers, adjust take-up tension, inspect coupling and gearbox, and verify skirt
board loading is centered.

Bearing wear at conveyor pulleys presents as rumbling noise, elevated bearing housing temperature,
and vibration at rotational frequency.
